    "objectives": "I want to support Cardano’s long-term success through serious, practical, and principles-driven governance. My priority is to protect decentralization, encourage strong open-source infrastructure, and support proposals that create clear long-term value for the ecosystem.",
    "motivations": "I became a DRep because I care deeply about Cardano’s future and would rather take responsibility for voting directly than outsource that judgment. I also wanted to offer a governance option for QUEEN delegators and others who value a grounded, long-term approach.",
    "qualifications": "I have been a Cardano holder since 2017 and an active contributor since 2019. I operate the Queen Ada stake pool, contribute as a builder in the ecosystem, and am the founder of Surf Lending."
